================================================================================
About the SDLU Android port
================================================================================

SDLU officially supports the Android platform. The port is built as part of the
Android project, just like SDL2. This is a fully functional port.


================================================================================
Requirements
================================================================================

* Android SDK (version 12 or later)
* Android NDK (r7 or later)
* An SDL2 android-project
* Good understanding of how the SDL2 android port works
* A bash shell (Windows users can use one of the many bash shells for Windows)


================================================================================
Preparation
================================================================================

* Create a new SDL2 android-project (as explained in SDL2/README-android.txt)
* Put SDL2_ttf at 'jni/SDL_ttf', and uncomment the following line from the SDL
  activity class (src/org/libsdl/app/SDLActivity.java -- line 45)

    System.loadLibrary("SDL2_ttf");


================================================================================
Patching the android-project
================================================================================

Open a terminal and type:

    $ cd /path/to/SDLU
    $ ./scripts/build-scripts/android.sh /path/to/android-project

The script will do the following in the android-project:
* Copy all source code files at 'jni/SDLU/src'
* Copy all header files at 'jni/SDLU/include'
* Edit 'src/org/libsdl/app/SDLActivity.java' to load SDLU at runtime
* Edit 'jni/src/Android.mk' to include SDLU

If SDLU is already installed in the android-project, and you just want to
update to the latest version, append 'update':

    $ ./scripts/build-scripts/android.sh /path/to/android-project update


================================================================================
Building the Android port
================================================================================

Assuming you have successfully patched the android-project as explained above,
you can now run 'ndk-build' to build your application.


-- Aggelos Kolaitis
